  "prompt": "Why did President Obama wait so long to show a birth certificate?",
  "response": "President Barack Obama released his long-form birth certificate in April 2011 to address persistent questions and conspiracy theories around his birthplace. Despite the fact that he had previously released a shorter form\u2014his Certificate of Live Birth from the state of Hawaii\u2014in 2008, some critics and \"birthers\" continued to insist that he was not born in the United States and was therefore ineligible to be president.\n\nObama and his administration had initially dismissed these claims as frivolous and politically motivated, believing that the existing documentation was sufficient to prove his citizenship. However, as the controversy continued and political opponents kept raising doubts, it became clear that releasing the long-form birth certificate could help to put the matter to rest more definitively. Eventually, Obama opted to take this step to alleviate the distraction and focus public discourse on more substantive policy issues.",
